      <media:content height="1532" medium="image" url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/03/24/multimedia/24re-IRELAND-PHONES-01-lzgc/24re-IRELAND-PHONES-01-lzgc-mediumSquareAt3X-v2.jpg" width="1532"></media:content>
      <media:description>The seaside town of Greystones, Ireland, is experimenting with a voluntary ban on smart devices for preteen children. Most of the town, from teachers to shopkeepers, is participating in one way or another.</media:description>
